    "_doc_deny": "DENY: production-WRITING operations + destructive deletes/drops. Tier C per autonomous-ops protocol — explicit user authorization each time. Override allow rules above. PROD READS NOT DENIED: per user directive 2026-05-06 ('Prod read should never be blocked. Only the write or update or delete is what we are looking out for') — drizzle-kit introspect, psql -c \"SELECT...\", neonctl connection-string production, vercel logs/inspect/env-ls etc. all flow through. Only WRITE-shape commands targeting prod connection-strings are denied below: drizzle-kit push (schema mutation), drizzle-kit drop, psql DROP/TRUNCATE/DELETE FROM... WHERE 1=1, vercel remove/rm/project rm, neonctl *delete*. NOTE: 'main' is intentionally NOT denied for git push here — this settings.json governs the TapAgents framework repo, which is main-only (no QA branch). User directive 2026-05-06: 'TapAgents can be pushed to main since we are always iterating it.' Other repos with prod gating inherit their own settings.json with main:* denied per `project_branch_strategy.md`.",
